dct_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Nottingham, solid and drift, sheet 126
dct_description_sm: Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 126 solid and drift. Geological Survey of Great Britain. North Decimal Degree 53.066700. South Decimal Degree 52.9167. East Decimal Degree -0.7667. West Decimal Degree -1.1833. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of Great Britain. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. "Original geological survey on the one-inch scale by W. T. Aveline, et al. Published on Sheets 71 N. E. (1858, additions 1879), 71 S.E. (1855, additions 1879), and 70 (1886), Old Series. Resurveyed on the six-inch scale in 1903-5 by B.S.N. Wilkinson, G. W. Lamplugh et al. Published with drift in 1908.".
dct_publisher_sm: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1908.
